{
  "texts": [
    "The datasetlevel imputation target is the conditionalP X mis | X obs, M ∝ P θ (X) P ϕ (M | X) P(θ) dθ,(1)from which samples yield plausible completions and conditional means provide point imputations.",
    "Focusing on a single record x i with mask m i, while borrowing strength from the entire dataset through the posterior over θ,P x mis i | x obs i, m i, X obs, M = P θ x mis i | x obs i, P(θ | X obs, M), dθ.",
    "(2)Under row i.i.d.",
    "assumptions, conditioning on θ factorizes across records:P θ X mis | X obs = n i=1 P θ x mis i | x obs i,so dependence across rows arises only from uncertainty in θ (or other shared latents) via P(θ | X obs, M).We use Rubin's taxonomy [30].",
    "In MCAR, missingness is independent of the data, P ϕ (M | X) = P ϕ (M); imputations can be accurate with well-calibrated uncertainty."
  ]
}